body:
It is a note of how to change the operation of the tab key in Textarea.

Usually, if you use a TAB key inside Textarea, the focus will move to the following input elements. Therefore, take the Keydown event and insert the `\ t` to the specified position.

### Actual code

#### app.component.html

`` `HTML
<FormGroup] = "Form" class = "form-control">
<TEXTAREA
#mdinput
FormControlname = "Markdown"
(Keydown) = "HandleKeydown ($ EVENT, MDINPUT)"
> </Textarea>
</form>
`` `

#### app.component.ts

`` `TS
Export Class AppComponent {
form = new formgroup ({
Markdown: New FormControl ('')
})

HandleKeydown (Event: KeyboardEvent, Mdinput: htmltextareaElement) {
if (event.key === 'tab') {
/** Tab elimination of focus transition when pressing the key* / / / /
Event.PreventDefault ();
/** Acquired the current cursor position from htmltextareaElement* / / /
CONST DEFAULTLOCATION = mdinput.Selectionstart;
CONST LEFT = This.form.controls.markdown.value.slice (0, mdinput.Selectionstart);
CONST RIGHT = This.form.controls.markdown.value.slice (mdinput.Selectionstart);
This.form.controls.markdown.setValue (Left + '\ T' + Right);
/** Move the cursor in the text area after Tab* /
mdinput.selectionend = defaultlocation + 1;
}
}
}
`` `

#### app.component.scss

The display width of `\ t` can be managed by the following CSS.

`` `SCSS
#mdinput {
Tab-size: 2;
}
`` `

You can see how this code is actually moving on the following screen.

